    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Jeffery's great. The problem with `ls .git*` and other `.dotfiles` is that the globbing semantics by default ignore hidden directories. This isn't a problem with `Get-ChildItem` because it can be passed `-Hidden`; but for globbing on *nix, I'll add a set of semantics to the globber to include hidden files (and return relative instead of absolute paths).\n",
